claim.claim-text:
1. An imaging apparatus, comprising:
an image-pickup lens;
a shutter partitioned into a plurality of sections along a first direction and allowed to open and close for each of the plurality of sections;
a stop adjusting an amount of light; and
a drive section driving the shutter and the stop, wherein the drive section controls the shutter in such a manner that at least one section of the plurality of sections of the shutter is opened and remaining sections of the plurality of sections are closed, and drives the stop in such a manner that a position of center of gravity of the opened section of the shutter is maintained at a substantially fixed position.
